<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Just to add a detail, Demaste could even enter the League of Shadows, as he fits the charter with his Race/Class/Deity.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
Just for the record, since we're being used as an example, if Demaste were a newborn roleplaying evil he would be welcome to apply to the League.  However if he had applied to us last month instead of the Harvesters, it would not have been that simple.  I don't think anybody in the League would be happy with someone switching from League of Honor to League of Shadows.  LoH being a neutral/good RP guild with a good reputation, it's clear Demaste couldn't have been a member of them if he were evil, therefore his past associations prove him to be ineligible to the League.  If he wished to roleplay something like a change of character (something which would have been impossible under the old alignment rules as alignments were set in stone once you reached 10) I suspect that would have been cause for a lot of debate and questions.<br>
<br>
I can't say what the final outcome would have been, but it would NOT have been as simple as you seem to be suggesting, and there is a definite possibility he would have been rejected.  It would certainly have been a very long, loud,  and heated debate involving the entire guild.<br>
<br>
/hijack off <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
